  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Clinical Impact on Point-of-Care Multiplex PCR Testing for Critically Ill Adult Patients With&#xD;
      Community-acquired Pneumonia - A cluster randomization study in ICU units within one medical&#xD;
      center.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Point-of-Care Multiplex PCR Testing could narrow down the pathogens causing severe&#xD;
      community-acquired pneumonia(CAP). Our hypothesis is that the result of Point-of-Care&#xD;
      Multiplex PCR Testing could help primary physician to reduce antibiotics use.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
